@reinvigorate_campaign
title: Reinvigorate the campaign
on-arrival: budget -= 1; reformer_approval += 4; moderate_approval += 2; hardliner_approval -= 4; popular_approval += 3; separatism += 1

The reinvigoration of the campaign will see harsher mandates against corruption than ever before. For most, the adjustment is expected, and welcome.

@maintain_campaign
title: Maintain the campaign
on-arrival: reformer_approval += 2; hardliner_approval -= 2; popular_approval += 1

While slightly underwhelming, the existing measures have been beneficial so far. Though
many among the reformers expected Gorbachev’s commitment to a harsher mandate, the continuation of a
positive campaign is an undoubtedly safe decision.

@scale_back
title: Scale-back the campaign
on-arrival: budget += 1; reformer_approval -= 3; moderate_approval -= 1; hardliner_approval += 2; popular_approval -= 2; separatism -= 1

All but the hardliners are displeased with our decision. This is unwelcome and
unexpected, in spite of the immediate increase in state funds accumulated by divesting from the campaign.
Our reputation must hang on other actions.

@abolish_campaign
title: Abolish the campaign
on-arrival: budget += 2; reformer_approval -= 4; moderate_approval -= 2; hardliner_approval += 4; popular_approval -= 4; separatism -= 2

While the reformers are left with hanging heads trying to figure just where it all went
wrong, the public wonders what this signals for the Kremlin’s inner operations. Trust built back by
Andropov is replaced with skepticism, for now.
